1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,000
MkvDrama.net

2
00:00:01,940 --> 00:00:03,040
Zen.

3
00:00:06,620 --> 00:00:07,800
I love you.

4
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:13,080
Me too.

5
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:16,100
I only want Ryo.

6
00:00:17,940 --> 00:00:19,040
It has to be Ryo.

7
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:21,580
Sorry.

8
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:27,000
I've... I've reached my limit.

9
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,610
I was just...

10
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,190
I think I was dreaming about the past.

11
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:24,750
Hm?

12
00:01:29,140 --> 00:01:31,400
We've really grown up, haven't we?

13
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,290
What's that about? So random.

14
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:40,200
Hey...

15
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:42,500
Yeah?

16
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:49,100
When I was falling asleep
last night, I was a little scared.

17
00:01:51,540 --> 00:01:52,900
Of what?

18
00:01:55,620 --> 00:02:00,300
That us becoming a couple
was all just a dream.

19
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:05,040
That I'd wake up in the morning...

20
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,700
and you wouldn't be in my arms.

21
00:02:22,660 --> 00:02:24,850
Are you still half-asleep?

22
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,810
Idiot.

23
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,360
I don't think...

24
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:47,150
I can ever let you go.

25
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:53,990
Well, can't be helped. I guess
I'll just have to make you happy.

26
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:00,020
You've got good taste, choosing me.

27
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:03,060
Right back at you.

28
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:09,700
Don't...

29
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,320
Stop that.

30
00:03:35,540 --> 00:03:36,580
Morning.

31
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,159
No matter how you slice
it, I won this round, right?

32
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,160
The only thing you won was the KPI.

33
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,239
In terms of profit, it was
a landslide victory for me.

34
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:54,760
All you did was
put on a routine, large-scale event.

35
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:57,799
But I brought in all new clients.

36
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,200
Yeah, yeah, whatever.
You just don't get it.

37
00:03:59,220 --> 00:04:01,059
The number of attendees
was double last year's.

38
00:04:01,060 --> 00:04:03,640
Isn't that just because you hired
a famous band to draw a crowd?

39
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,600
That's playing on easy mode.

40
00:04:04,601 --> 00:04:06,500
Uh, okay, that's enough, you two.

41
00:04:06,740 --> 00:04:08,080
What?

42
00:04:08,660 --> 00:04:10,000
Yes, sorry.

43
00:04:11,540 --> 00:04:15,750
I can't believe a socially awkward
guy like you could earn an artist's trust.

44
00:04:15,790 --> 00:04:16,520
Huh?

45
00:04:16,521 --> 00:04:18,319
I've had no problem with it so far.

46
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,479
Speaking of which.

47
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:21,829
You only won back the top spot once.

48
00:04:21,830 --> 00:04:23,759
Are you sure you should
be getting this cocky?

49
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:24,959
What?

50
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:27,640
Listen, the competition was
about the KPI from the start.

51
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:29,010
So I won.

52
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:30,220
Got it?

53
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,180
I refuse to accept that.

54
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,619
Pretty amazing, right?

55
00:04:36,620 --> 00:04:38,320
Yes, very.

56
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:41,586
I was just thinking Yotsuya-san
was back from his business trip.

57
00:04:41,610 --> 00:04:43,310
And he comes back to this.

58
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:47,120
They really fight like little kids.

59
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,450
Yeah.

60
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:50,700
Especially since they're
both so brilliant at work.

61
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,139
I should get back.

62
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:10,440
Just one more minute.

63
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:15,330
- That's enough.
- Ow.

64
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,600
How many times have I told you?

65
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,760
I want to focus on work
when I'm at the office.

66
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:20,189
I've been away on business.

67
00:05:20,190 --> 00:05:21,360
We've barely seen each other.

68
00:05:22,220 --> 00:05:23,150
A little moment can't hurt, can it?

69
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:25,020
This has nothing to do with your trip.

70
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:27,700
I said not at the office.

71
00:05:33,740 --> 00:05:34,840
I've told you before.

72
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:41,020
If this keeps up, I won't be
able to concentrate on my work.

73
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:46,739
Then when we get home
tonight, we can continue...

74
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:48,860
Because of how you just
acted, tonight's canceled.

75
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:54,940
Just kidding.

76
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,440
Don't you complain, even if
we're up late tonight, okay?

77
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:05,300
"Fake Fact Lips"

78
00:07:05,993 --> 00:07:08,893
(Episode 6: The "After All" Is Unnecessary)

79
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:11,199
Yotsuya-san, I've been
looking all over for you.

80
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,519
Sorry, sorry.

81
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:15,839
Senshin Publisher just sent
over the production schedule.

82
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:18,280
But it seems a little different
from the one we made before.

83
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:22,019
Oh, didn't the client
send an email about some changes?

84
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:22,900
That must be it.

85
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:25,320
Huh? Let me check.

86
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,299
- Yotsuya.
- Yes?

87
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,020
About the meeting this evening.

88
00:07:28,021 --> 00:07:29,460
I'd still like you to be there.

89
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,470
Huh?

90
00:07:30,471 --> 00:07:34,500
Uh, it starts at five, right?

91
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,839
Would it be okay if I'm a little late?

92
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:38,940
Not a problem at all.

93
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,500
That's a huge help. Thank you.

94
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,200
Yotsuya-san, excuse me.

95
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,319
I found the email.

96
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:45,130
See? Told you.

97
00:07:45,230 --> 00:07:46,010
Yotsuya-san.

98
00:07:46,011 --> 00:07:48,289
The client wants to add a few
more options for the brand colors.

99
00:07:48,290 --> 00:07:49,820
Ah, of course.

100
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,930
I knew this would happen.

101
00:07:51,970 --> 00:07:53,510
So I've already made a list.

102
00:07:53,550 --> 00:07:55,679
Um... tell them we can get it
to them by the end of the day.

103
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,800
Okay, I'll let them know.

104
00:07:58,220 --> 00:07:59,220
Oh, by the way.

105
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:00,070
Tonight.

106
00:08:00,071 --> 00:08:02,919
Saeki-san from Gaisei
company invited me out for drinks.

107
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,619
Would you be able to join me?

108
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:06,110
Saeki-san, huh?

109
00:08:06,150 --> 00:08:06,980
Yes.

110
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,430
He specifically told me to
bring you along, Yotsuya-san.

111
00:08:10,540 --> 00:08:12,119
- I'll pass.
- What?

112
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,499
Because if he gets a hold of you,

113
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:15,399
you won't get home until morning.

114
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,199
That's why I don't want to go alone!

115
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,320
If it's just for drinks, you don't need me.

116
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:22,160
Look, isn't that guy from your year?

117
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,959
I refuse.

118
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:25,039
Why not?

119
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,359
Because there's a game I want
to play as soon as I get home.

120
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,580
So heartless.

121
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:30,739
Please don't leave me to fend for myself.

122
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:32,159
He's your client.

123
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,119
I'll make it up to you, I promise.

124
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:36,180
- No.
- Why?

125
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:40,140
Because someone's waiting for me at home.

126
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:43,950
Someone at home?

127
00:08:45,690 --> 00:08:46,490
What?!

128
00:08:46,491 --> 00:08:48,860
Yotsuya-san, you're seeing someone?

129
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,279
Give us the details!

130
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:52,300
What is it? Don't all crowd around.

131
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:53,779
- Go on, shoo.
- Since when?

132
00:08:53,780 --> 00:08:54,939
Where did you meet?

133
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:55,920
What are they like?

134
00:08:55,921 --> 00:08:57,069
Is it someone from the company?

135
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:57,930
From the Secretarial department?

136
00:08:57,930 --> 00:08:58,680
Or General Affairs?

137
00:08:58,680 --> 00:08:59,630
From another company?

138
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:00,350
Are they older than you?

139
00:09:00,351 --> 00:09:01,459
Younger?

140
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:02,569
What's their type?

141
00:09:02,570 --> 00:09:04,000
So annoying!

142
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:18,320
Someone respectable and cute, I bet.

143
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:31,730
You...

144
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:35,040
Don't say weird things at the office.

145
00:09:36,219 --> 00:09:37,419
What's the big deal?

146
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:40,000
I just said I have a partner.

147
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,900
That may be true, but...

148
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:45,780
It's not like anyone
would guess I'm with Zen.

149
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:48,880
Hey.

150
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,740
Let me finish my drink first.

151
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:54,590
Stop messing around.

152
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,770
Again?

153
00:10:00,180 --> 00:10:01,820
I've been holding back for so long.

154
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:04,459
Then you need to hold
back when you're at the office.

155
00:10:04,460 --> 00:10:06,060
I was wrong about that.

156
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,800
It's been so long
since I saw you, I just...

157
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,210
No excuses.

158
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:15,570
I'm sorry.

159
00:10:16,860 --> 00:10:18,090
I'll be more careful.

160
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:27,000
If I can't focus on work because of you,

161
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:30,420
then we'll have less time
to spend together, won't we?

162
00:10:34,710 --> 00:10:35,760
Zen.

163
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:40,590
You're trying to make time for me, too?

164
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,040
Of course.

165
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:44,840
I've also felt bad for being so busy
and neglecting you.

166
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:48,580
After all, we are a couple, aren't we?

167
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:52,430
The "after all" is unnecessary.

168
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:08,680
I can't hold back much longer.

169
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,639
Just let me enjoy my drink a little longer.

170
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:13,210
If I let you enjoy your drink,

171
00:11:13,420 --> 00:11:15,590
you'll just pass out right away.

172
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:22,240
Well, that depends on
your performance, Ryo.

173
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,539
Huh?

174
00:11:23,540 --> 00:11:24,640
What did you say?

175
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:30,759
I'll do my best, so hurry up and drink.

176
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,420
I get it, calm down.

177
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:33,460
Sit down first.

178
00:11:34,310 --> 00:11:37,149
- I'll do my best.
- I know you will.

179
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:38,459
So put your clothes back on first.

180
00:11:38,460 --> 00:11:40,116
We're just going to take
them off again anyway.

181
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:41,699
- Stand up.
- Oh, honestly.

182
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:42,620
Okay, okay, I get it.

183
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:43,620
Come on, your hand.

184
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,989
- Let's go.
- Seriously.

185
00:11:46,990 --> 00:11:48,820
Don't you "seriously" me.

186
00:12:24,330 --> 00:12:25,660
Still awake?

187
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:30,350
Barely.

188
00:12:42,110 --> 00:12:43,310
So, this quarter...

189
00:12:45,030 --> 00:12:46,720
Zen won, right?

190
00:12:48,010 --> 00:12:49,010
Yeah.

191
00:12:50,950 --> 00:12:52,910
Is there anything you want me to do?

192
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:54,600
Uh...

193
00:12:56,690 --> 00:12:58,580
I don't think so.

194
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:01,360
What?

195
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:03,370
How boring.

196
00:13:04,570 --> 00:13:08,370
Competing with someone who isn't even
that upset about losing...

197
00:13:08,410 --> 00:13:10,290
is pretty boring for me, too.

198
00:13:12,150 --> 00:13:16,330
You're the one who came up
with the rule in the first place.

199
00:13:17,290 --> 00:13:20,150
I never had anything I
particularly wanted you to do.

200
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,070
Yeah, yeah, I know.

201
00:13:24,570 --> 00:13:26,650
Because no matter the outcome,

202
00:13:27,326 --> 00:13:29,286
it's a reward for you either way, right?

203
00:13:30,950 --> 00:13:32,050
That's true.

204
00:13:33,290 --> 00:13:34,810
You know me so well.

205
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:40,960
Ah, but if I had to say something...

206
00:13:41,530 --> 00:13:42,530
Hm?

207
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,420
I want to know more about you.

208
00:13:49,530 --> 00:13:50,550
Huh?

209
00:13:50,710 --> 00:13:53,210
Ryo, you know a lot about me.

210
00:13:54,430 --> 00:13:57,950
But I know almost nothing
about you from college.

211
00:14:00,530 --> 00:14:03,830
That's because you never asked.

212
00:14:04,460 --> 00:14:05,460
Also...

213
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:07,629
I'm also still hung up on you
saying you like sleeping with men.

214
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:08,840
No, that's not it.

215
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:09,969
I was just bluffing.

216
00:14:09,970 --> 00:14:11,460
I'm sure that's not true.

217
00:14:12,970 --> 00:14:16,240
I don't mean to bring up old stuff, but...

218
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:19,309
This whole arrangement
is skewed in your favor.

219
00:14:19,310 --> 00:14:20,460
It's not fair at all.

220
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:24,130
But...

221
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:28,490
There are so many things I want Zen to do.

222
00:14:30,350 --> 00:14:32,029
If I didn't do it this way, you
never would have agreed.

223
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:33,070
I didn't have a choice.

224
00:14:33,490 --> 00:14:35,750
What else do you want me to do?

225
00:14:36,550 --> 00:14:37,550
Hmm...

226
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:42,840
Make you list 10 things you like about me.

227
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:44,770
Who could even come up with that?

228
00:14:45,070 --> 00:14:46,989
See? Again, it only benefits you.

229
00:14:46,990 --> 00:14:50,490
Then think of something that
would make me uncomfortable.

230
00:14:52,330 --> 00:14:53,330
Ah.

231
00:14:54,010 --> 00:14:54,890
What is it?

232
00:14:54,890 --> 00:14:55,670
It's nothing.

233
00:14:55,810 --> 00:14:57,770
I just thought of something
completely unrelated.

234
00:14:58,190 --> 00:14:59,190
What is it?

235
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,180
What's this?

236
00:15:10,790 --> 00:15:11,790
Rid Randal?!

237
00:15:12,820 --> 00:15:13,490
Why?

238
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:16,130
It's nothing. I got them from a work event.

239
00:15:16,450 --> 00:15:17,280
- Want to go together?
- Huh?

240
00:15:17,281 --> 00:15:20,240
Did I ever tell you I like them?

241
00:15:20,330 --> 00:15:21,080
Oh, really?

242
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,080
Huh? It's just a coincidence?!

243
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:22,730
Yeah.

244
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:23,510
Seriously?

245
00:15:23,511 --> 00:15:26,029
I've been a huge fan
of theirs since college.

246
00:15:26,030 --> 00:15:27,550
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

247
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,980
They've gotten so popular lately.

248
00:15:29,990 --> 00:15:31,949
It's impossible to get concert
tickets, even through the lottery.

249
00:15:31,950 --> 00:15:35,269
I didn't win the lottery back
then, so I'd already given up.

250
00:15:35,270 --> 00:15:36,599
I can't believe you managed to get tickets.

251
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,746
They were a thank-you gift
for helping with a dispute.

252
00:15:38,770 --> 00:15:39,889
Seriously?

253
00:15:39,890 --> 00:15:41,410
Wow, that's amazing.

254
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,360
It's been so long since I've been to one.

255
00:15:44,030 --> 00:15:46,530
You know, this is our
first proper date, isn't it?

256
00:15:46,690 --> 00:15:49,049
If this is a date, it's
going to be a blast.

257
00:15:49,050 --> 00:15:50,086
The energy is going to be insane.

258
00:15:50,110 --> 00:15:51,150
Rid Randal.

259
00:15:51,290 --> 00:15:53,869
Actually, I tried to
book them for our event.

260
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:56,030
But their schedule was completely full.

261
00:15:56,070 --> 00:15:57,419
They're my absolute favorite right now.

262
00:15:57,420 --> 00:15:59,649
Lately, I've been singing
Rid Randal at karaoke.

263
00:15:59,650 --> 00:16:01,920
Rid Randal, Rid Randal...

264
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:04,419
Rid Randal, Rid Randal...
I just can't stop.

265
00:16:04,420 --> 00:16:05,250
Okay.

266
00:16:05,251 --> 00:16:07,550
Okay, I think the file
should be shareable soon.

267
00:16:07,610 --> 00:16:08,610
Okay.

268
00:16:09,730 --> 00:16:11,410
- Okay.
- The documents just arrived.

269
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,190
Yes, I'll send it to you now.
Okay, goodbye.

270
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:14,250
Here you go.

271
00:16:14,330 --> 00:16:15,770
Thanks.
Oh, by the way.

272
00:16:15,930 --> 00:16:17,349
How's that proposal coming along?

273
00:16:17,350 --> 00:16:20,070
Ah, well, there's about 80% left.

274
00:16:20,570 --> 00:16:21,649
Huh? You've only done 20%?

275
00:16:21,650 --> 00:16:22,769
Ah, I misspoke... Um...

276
00:16:22,770 --> 00:16:25,050
I've finished 80%, so
there's only about 20% left.

277
00:16:25,350 --> 00:16:26,370
I see. Show it to me when you're done.

278
00:16:26,390 --> 00:16:28,070
Okay, I'll finish it right away.

279
00:16:28,430 --> 00:16:29,430
No rush. Take your time.

280
00:16:29,470 --> 00:16:30,470
Yes, sir.

281
00:16:44,090 --> 00:16:45,700
Do you have plans later?

282
00:16:47,290 --> 00:16:48,370
Nothing in particular.

283
00:16:52,290 --> 00:16:53,650
Are you going on a date?

284
00:16:54,810 --> 00:16:55,480
Huh?

285
00:16:55,550 --> 00:16:58,110
First Yotsuya-san, and now you're
going on a date too, Shido-san?

286
00:16:58,680 --> 00:16:59,810
What if I am?

287
00:17:00,190 --> 00:17:01,290
What?!

288
00:17:02,170 --> 00:17:03,270
Shido-san.

289
00:17:03,310 --> 00:17:06,080
Are you even competing with Yotsuya-san
over who has a girlfriend?

290
00:17:06,170 --> 00:17:07,250
I would never do something like that.

291
00:17:07,270 --> 00:17:09,510
But the timing is a little
too perfect, don't you think?

292
00:17:09,770 --> 00:17:10,730
It's just a coincidence.

293
00:17:10,731 --> 00:17:12,149
You're even busier with work than we are.

294
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:13,860
How did you get a girlfriend?

295
00:17:14,170 --> 00:17:15,250
Please, teach me your ways.

296
00:17:17,410 --> 00:17:18,930
Don't you have a girlfriend?

297
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,240
We broke up.

298
00:17:21,330 --> 00:17:21,840
Huh?

299
00:17:21,910 --> 00:17:23,040
Seriously?

300
00:17:23,080 --> 00:17:24,736
Weren't you together for about three years?

301
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:26,740
Yeah, since we were students.

302
00:17:28,390 --> 00:17:30,190
Work has been too busy lately.

303
00:17:30,630 --> 00:17:33,590
It's amazing how
quickly you can drift apart.

304
00:17:34,190 --> 00:17:36,770
I hate to admit it, but
that's pretty common.

305
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:38,050
Yeah.

306
00:17:39,470 --> 00:17:41,050
You should be careful too, Shido-san.

307
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:43,190
The time you get to
spend together is precious.

308
00:17:43,890 --> 00:17:44,990
I know.

309
00:17:46,490 --> 00:17:47,690
More importantly, Higashino.

310
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:50,350
I said no rush,
but get back to work.

311
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:51,780
Yes! Sorry!

312
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:53,689
That's right, Higashino.

313
00:17:53,690 --> 00:17:55,110
No need to rush, just hurry up.

314
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,200
Yes, sir.

315
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:58,280
Huh?

316
00:17:59,410 --> 00:18:00,410
Okay.

317
00:18:11,370 --> 00:18:13,010
Okay, it's done.

318
00:18:14,630 --> 00:18:15,340
Shido-san.

319
00:18:15,340 --> 00:18:16,340
Yeah?

320
00:18:16,550 --> 00:18:17,770
Could you please check this?

321
00:18:17,970 --> 00:18:19,740
Ah, one second.

322
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:26,000
Yeah, just swap this part
and this part, and it'll be fine.

323
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:27,560
Got it.

324
00:18:27,580 --> 00:18:28,580
Thank you very much.

325
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,910
- I'll be heading out then.
- See you.

326
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:38,720
Hello, this is Shido.

327
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:42,120
Ah, thank you for your help the other day.

328
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:43,780
Yes.

329
00:18:46,370 --> 00:18:47,370
Yes.

330
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:50,720
I see.

331
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:18,200
(A client called me in last minute. I probably
won't make it until after the show. Sorry.)

332
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:28,410
Yotsuya-san?

333
00:19:52,810 --> 00:19:53,910
Ah, Shido.

334
00:19:55,260 --> 00:19:56,260
You actually made it.

335
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:57,530
Sorry, I missed it.

336
00:19:57,570 --> 00:19:59,820
It's fine, don't worry about it.

337
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,380
By the way...

338
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:03,560
Oh, right, right.

339
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,199
I just ran into
Kiritani-san and her friend.

340
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,320
Yeah.

341
00:20:07,380 --> 00:20:09,559
We bumped into each other at
the entrance. It was such a surprise.

342
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:11,240
Oh, so that's what happened.

343
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:12,940
- It's been a while.
- It has.

344
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,140
Long time no see.

345
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:16,100
Huh?

346
00:20:16,580 --> 00:20:19,050
Could it be Shido-san?

347
00:20:19,340 --> 00:20:20,550
Huh? What do you mean?

348
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:24,030
Ah, Yotsuya-san just mentioned
that someone couldn't make it today.

349
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,850
We thought it might
have been his girlfriend.

350
00:20:27,390 --> 00:20:28,799
No, that's not it.

351
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:31,120
It's a shame you couldn't be
here for the show, Shido-san.

352
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:34,310
The chorus of the fourth
song was incredible, wasn't it?

353
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:35,539
- Totally incredible.
- Right?

354
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:37,159
You know, that song from the album.

355
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,859
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- The intro was completely different.

356
00:20:38,860 --> 00:20:40,299
- Different.
- The arrangement was amazing.

357
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:41,879
- Amazing.
- I know, right?

358
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:42,740
- Huh, you noticed?

359
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:43,220
Well...

360
00:20:43,570 --> 00:20:46,470
Don't tell me you're a fan too, Shido-san?

361
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:49,010
Huh?

362
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:51,540
Oh, no, I don't know them at all.

363
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:54,056
It's just that Yotsuya seems to
have been a fan for a long time.

364
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,320
Yeah.

365
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:56,960
She's a huge fan too.

366
00:20:57,140 --> 00:20:59,380
We had a great time
talking with Yotsuya-san.

367
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:01,819
And they both know even
more about them than I do.

368
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:03,160
Is that so?

369
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:07,640
This was my first time really
talking with Yotsuya-san.

370
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:09,700
He's a really interesting person.

371
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:12,259
That guy didn't say anything rude, did he?

372
00:21:12,260 --> 00:21:13,860
Of course not. Not at all.

373
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:15,519
He even apologized, saying...

374
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:18,000
that you were the
one who got the tickets.

375
00:21:18,650 --> 00:21:19,680
Oh, I see.

376
00:21:19,860 --> 00:21:21,260
By the way, since we're all here...

377
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:23,219
Want to go for a drink later?

378
00:21:23,220 --> 00:21:24,790
Oh, sure...

379
00:21:27,950 --> 00:21:28,950
What do you think?

380
00:21:29,620 --> 00:21:30,620
Ah...

381
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:32,099
Um...

382
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:35,379
- Hey, but...
- Oh, sorry.

383
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:36,659
Oh, no, it's really okay.

384
00:21:36,660 --> 00:21:39,670
But maybe next time.
Let's do it again sometime.

385
00:21:39,710 --> 00:21:40,710
Yeah, you're right.

386
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,800
Shido-san, you have to
come with us next time.

387
00:21:43,090 --> 00:21:43,800
Okay.

388
00:21:43,900 --> 00:21:45,580
I'll do my homework before then.

389
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:48,620
Okay, well, we'll get going then.

390
00:21:48,660 --> 00:21:49,990
- Bye.
- Okay.

391
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:55,479
Matsushita-san, the
one with Kiritani-san...

392
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:56,900
is hilarious.

393
00:21:57,180 --> 00:21:59,019
During the most hype song of the concert...

394
00:21:59,020 --> 00:22:00,460
she suddenly started headbanging.

395
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:02,840
I teased her, like, "This
isn't that kind of song."

396
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,440
And Kiritani-san was just stunned.

397
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:08,410
The look on her face was priceless.

398
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,420
Zen?

399
00:22:15,460 --> 00:22:16,520
Hey? Zen?

400
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,516
What's wrong? Are you mad?

401
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:20,420
I'm not mad.

402
00:22:20,421 --> 00:22:21,541
You sure don't look like it.

403
00:22:22,670 --> 00:22:23,670
What's wrong?

404
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:27,120
Huh?

405
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:28,170
You're not... jealous, are you?

406
00:22:28,170 --> 00:22:29,010
What?

407
00:22:29,180 --> 00:22:30,340
No way.

408
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:31,400
You totally are.

409
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:35,490
Is it because I was having
fun talking with them?

410
00:22:35,890 --> 00:22:36,890
Give me a break.

411
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:38,279
It's not that.

412
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:42,310
Honestly, I didn't think
you'd get so jealous.

413
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:45,710
Whatever. I'm just a petty guy.

414
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:47,360
I'm going home.

415
00:22:47,950 --> 00:22:49,440
If that's the case, then I'm sorry.

416
00:22:49,700 --> 00:22:51,359
I'm not mad at you.

417
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:52,360
Huh?

418
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:57,000
I... I can't believe I didn't know
what kind of music you like.

419
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:59,250
No, that doesn't matter at all...

420
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:04,920
I thought I wouldn't care
no matter who you were friendly with.

421
00:23:07,340 --> 00:23:08,790
You're nice to everyone.

422
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:11,530
Such a charmer.

423
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:13,850
See? You are mad at me.

424
00:23:13,890 --> 00:23:14,890
No.

425
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:16,080
It's just...

426
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:19,300
Getting jealous over
something so trivial at this point.

427
00:23:19,390 --> 00:23:20,870
I can't even control my own emotions.

428
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:22,310
I feel so pathetic.

429
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,500
Let's just call it a day.

430
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,170
I'll probably calm down after a while.

431
00:23:33,616 --> 00:23:35,300
There's no way I'm leaving you like this.

432
00:24:06,690 --> 00:24:07,820
Morning.

433
00:24:20,740 --> 00:24:21,870
Yo, Shido-kun.

434
00:24:22,780 --> 00:24:24,080
Long time no see.

435
00:24:25,290 --> 00:24:26,460
Futami?

436
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:33,040
Futami... you...

437
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:51,800
(Next episode)

438
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:52,939
(Episode 7: Let Me In On This Match!)
It's a pleasure to be working with you.

439
00:25:52,940 --> 00:25:55,509
Futami's transfer was so sudden.

440
00:25:55,510 --> 00:25:57,179
Now that he's back...

441
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:59,219
Looks like things are
about to get lively again.

442
00:25:59,220 --> 00:26:01,600
Hey, Shido~

443
00:26:01,620 --> 00:26:03,519
I look forward to working with you again.

444
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:04,769
Yeah, same here.

445
00:26:04,770 --> 00:26:06,259
You two are still in touch?

446
00:26:06,260 --> 00:26:08,039
You're still as close as ever.

447
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:10,110
We even go on trips
together, just the two of us.

448
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,280
Trips?

449
00:26:11,281 --> 00:26:12,639
Let's have a drink, just the two of us.

450
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:13,649
Why are you going this far?

451
00:26:13,650 --> 00:26:14,580
Do you really have to
make this a competition?

452
00:26:14,581 --> 00:26:17,920
Because I'm a better match
for Yotsuya-san than you are.

453
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,880
You're staying the night, right?

454
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:20,880
MkvDrama.net

